[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "71:1-13 David prays that he might never be made ashamed of dependence upon God. With this petition every true believer may come boldly to the throne of grace. The gracious care of Divine providence in our birth and infancy, should engage us to early piety. He that was our Help from our birth, ought to be our Hope from our youth. Let none expect ease or comfort from the world. Those who love the Lord, often are hated and persecuted; men wondered at for their principles and conduct; but the Lord has been their strong refuge. The faithful servants of God may be assured that he will not cast them off in old age, nor forsake them when their strength fails.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For mine enemies speak against me - That is, they said substantially, as it is stated in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 71:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", that God had forsaken him, and that therefore, they would arise and punish him, or treat him as an outcast from God.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And they that lay wait for my soul - For my life; or, to take my life. The margin here - as the Hebrew - is, \"watch,\" or \"observe.\" The \"watchers for my life;\" that is, they who watch for an opportunity to take my life, or to destroy me.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Take counsel together - About the best means of accomplishing their object. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Take counsel together - About the best means of accomplishing their object. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
