  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For mine enemies speak against, me,.... Or \"say unto me\" (y) what is expressed in the following verse, \"God hath forsaken him\"; and so these words are a reason of the above petitions: or \"mine enemies speak to me\"; or \"of me\" (z); not good, but evil, and so the Targum paraphrases it, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"for mine enemies speak evil against me;'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or concerning me. David had his enemies, and many, as Ahithophel, and others, who spake against him to the people, and thereby drew many with them into rebellion against him; and particularly Shimei spoke against him, and cursed him, calling him a bloody man, a man of Belial, 2 Samuel 16:7; ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "or concerning me. David had his enemies, and many, as Ahithophel, and others, who spake against him to the people, and thereby drew many with them into rebellion against him; and particularly Shimei spoke against him, and cursed him, calling him a bloody man, a man of Belial, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 16:7",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and they that lay wait for my soul; or \"life\"; that laid snares for him; or lay in ambush, and sought for an opportunity to take away his life: or \"they that keep my soul\", or \"life\" (a); that were his bodyguards that were about his person for the preservation of him; and so the Targum seems to understand it; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "take counsel together; lay schemes and form plots how to destroy him, as Ahithophel did, 2 Samuel 16:20. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "take counsel together; lay schemes and form plots how to destroy him, as Ahithophel did, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 16:20",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(y)  \"dixerunt mihi\", Montanus. (z) \"De me loquuti sunt, vel loquuntur\", Tigurine version, Junius & Tremellius, Gejerus, Michaelis. (a)  \"custodientes animam meam\", Pagninus, Montanus; \"custodiebant\", V. L. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(y)  \"dixerunt mihi\", Montanus. (z) \"De me loquuti sunt, vel loquuntur\", Tigurine version, Junius & Tremellius, Gejerus, Michaelis. (a)  \"custodientes animam meam\", Pagninus, Montanus; \"custodiebant\", V. L. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
